alert.note: Alert for Grays Harbor (Washington) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: Flood Warning issued December 05 at 5:12AM PST until December 05 at 8:55PM PST by NWS Seattle
info.description: ...The National Weather Service in Seattle WA has issued a Flood Warning for the following rivers in Washington... Satsop River Near Satsop affecting Grays Harbor County. .Heavy rain over the south slopes of the Olympics will come to an end late this morning. For the Olympic Peninsula Region...including Satsop...Minor flooding is forecast. ...FLOOD WARNING IN EFFECT FROM THIS MORNING TO THIS EVENING... * WHAT...Minor flooding is forecast. * WHERE...Satsop River near Satsop. * WHEN...From this morning to this evening. * IMPACTS...At 38.0 feet, the Satsop River will flood low pasture lands and some roads along the river. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 4:15 AM PST Tuesday the stage was 36.8 feet. - Flood stage is 38.0 feet. - Forecast...The river will crest around 38.1 feet late this morning then fall back below flood stage this afternoon. - http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood &&
info.instruction: Turn around, don`t drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood deaths occur in vehicles. Motorists should not attempt to drive around barricades or drive cars through flooded areas. Additional information is available at www.weather.gov. The next statement will be issued by this afternoon at 115 PM PST.
